external_knowledge:
- 'young enterprises' refers to companies that went public after the year 2000;
- 'tech sector' is represented by sector ID 1;
- 'debuted on the stock market' means the company's IPO year;
- 'ordered from the most recent to the oldest' means sorted by IPO year in descending order.

sql:
SELECT portfolio_id, COUNT(DISTINCT company_id) AS company_count
FROM portfolio_companies
GROUP BY portfolio_id;

SELECT company_id, AVG(revenue) AS average_revenue
FROM company_financials
GROUP BY company_id;
